==English==

===Pronunciation===

:met' â morph' ik
:met' â morph' is im

===Etymology===

:From Greek, something that has changed in form. 

===Noun===
'''Metamorphism''' 
#The process by which [[rock]]s are changed into other forms by the application of heat and/or pressure.

===Adjective===
'''Metamorphic'''
#A rock that has been changed from its original form by subjection to heat and/or pressure.

:There are many stages of metamorphism. A rock that has been mildly changed will still show its original bedding planes and other features. A rock that has been severely changed may no longer resemble its source rock at all.

